                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/48.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">O’Shaughnessy</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 22, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>735. Referring to Department’s 618, January 21. Many complaints are coming to
                    this Embassy regarding forced loans upon <pb facs="0887" n="771" xml:id="pg_771"
                    /> American citizens. I have already advised Americans more or less in the sense
                    of Department’s 618, January 21, but I have the honor to respectfully suggest
                    that I be authorized to enter a formal protest with the Mexican de facto
                    government in the premises.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson O’Shaughnessy</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
